# Shell scripts must stay LF on every platform. The bash updater
# (99 - Meta/04 - Tooling/update-vault.sh) ships to macOS/Linux adopters, where a
# CRLF checkout turns its shebang into "#!/usr/bin/env bash\r" -> "bad
# interpreter". Without this pin a Windows contributor with core.autocrlf=true
# could commit CRLF and silently break the bash updater on exactly the platforms
# it exists for. ADR 0002 keeps that bash updater a first-class implementation,
# so its line endings are a correctness contract, not a preference.
*.sh text eol=lf

# The manifest is generated LF by generate-manifest.ps1 and parsed line-by-line
# by the bash updater's sed; keep it LF for the same reason.
framework-manifest.json text eol=lf
